' plan-35-A: `term::sync()` is the present hook. In the Phase A scaffold it is a
' clean no-op. This fixture proves the new builtin is emitted, dispatched, and
' returns cleanly at runtime on every backend: calling it while TUI mode is off
' does nothing and is harmless, and the program exits 0. (The escape-emitting
' `term::on`/`term::off` path is compile-covered by tests/syntax/term/term-valid
' and gains its runtime present coverage in plan-35-C.)
IMPORT term
IMPORT io

FUNC main AS Integer
  io::print("before")
  ' No-op while TUI mode is off — nothing is presented.
  term::sync()
  term::sync()
  io::print("after")
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
